# Recent ElizaOS Repository Updates

The ElizaOS repository has seen numerous updates focused primarily on bug fixes, linting improvements, and some feature additions. Here's a summary of the recent changes:

## Bug Fixes

### Image and Vision Services
- Fixed ImageVisionModelProvider not being applied in runtime for image description service (PR #3056)
- Fixed handling of unsupported image providers (PR #3057)
- Fixed LLaVA model parsing issue (PR #3008)

### Client and UI Improvements
- Fixed auto-scrolling issue in client (PR #3115)
- Fixed message ID collision in Telegram Client (PR #3053)
- Fixed JSON parsing error when an array is a value in JSON (PR #3113)

### Service Improvements
- Changed handleAnthropic default mode to auto (PR #3018)
- Fixed deepgram transcription null check (PR #3014)
- Improved service startup by preventing services from starting twice and improving logging (PR #3007)
- Fixed client-slack & adapter-postgres connection between user and room (PR #3006)

## Linting and Code Quality

## New Features

- Added Aggregator swap for SUI tokens (PR #3012)
- Added Fleek Eliza deployment to Chinese README (PR #3048)
- Added Arabic translation for README (PR #3081)
- Added demo API access for CoinGecko (PR #3050)
- Added test configuration and coverage for various plugins (PRs #3072, #3068, #3064)

## Documentation

- Added "What Did You Get Done This Week? 11" notes (PR #3103)
- Improved navigation section links in packages/adapters documentation (PR #3005)

## Other Improvements

- Fixed Docker build command by skipping eslint files (PR #3110)
- Updated .gitignore and removed build files (PR #3117)
- Fixed export of dexScreenerPlugin (PR #3120)
- Removed duplicate litPlugin import (PR #3121)
- Fixed spelling issues (PR #3041)
- Fixed regex (PR #3054)

categories.title: Recent Issues in the elizaOS/eliza GitHub Repository

content.text: The elizaOS/eliza GitHub repository has several open issues related to new feature requests and integration proposals. Users have requested adding Edwin integration (#3040), creating a Safe wallet plugin (#3058), and adding demo API access to the CoinGecko plugin (#3049). There's also a request to add AI/ML API as a provider (#3047). These feature requests show community interest in expanding the platform's capabilities.

Several users are experiencing authentication and connection issues with the platform. These include authentication failures with the Deepseek API (#3013), Twitter login failures (#3112), and connection problems with the Anthropic model (#3079). There's also a module import error reported where the system cannot find '@elizaos/core' (#3108). These technical issues highlight some challenges users are facing when trying to use the platform.

There are also issues related to documentation and testing. Issue #3123 focuses on testing configuration and coverage for the CoinGecko plugin, while issue #3083 proposes adding a new troubleshooting FAQ section to the documentation. These issues indicate ongoing efforts to improve the platform's reliability and user experience.
